A more recent study, as described above, concluded a 4.8-day incubation period (3.0-7.2) based on a population of 8 866 cases.
It is very important that health authorities adjust the actual duration of quarantine according to a specified period of incubation, in order to prevent infected but asymptomatic people from transmitting the virus.
