COVID-19 affects older people more than young people and more men than women; severity and mortality rates are also greater among older people.
SARS has a higher mortality than VOCID-19 (10.91 per cent versus 1.44 per cent).
The transmission of the COVID-19 virus is possible even in the absence of symptoms, while SARS was mostly transmitted by patients with severe disease, so it is much more difficult to contain the spread of COVID-19.
This explains in part why SARS-CoV-2 spread much faster and much more widely than SARS-COV.
